Name: os_lastreg
Author: n00bie
Category: OperServ
Last updated: 2007-08-26T19:21:48+01:00

This module will retrieve the last nickname and channel registered. This command if given with a [b]nick[/b] param will display the last registered nickname and the registered time. Likewise if given with the [b]chan[/b] param will display the last registered channel, registered time and the founder of the channel if available.
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
[b]Providing Command:[/b]

/msg OperServ HELP LASTREG
/msg OperServ LASTREG nick|chan

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
[b]NOTE:[/b]
This module is my first module using a seperate database, so don\'t think that this module is intelligent enough to retrieve the last registered nickname/channel at the time of loading this module. It will ONLY retrieve if a new nickname/channel is registered after loading or using this module ;-)
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Module suggested by ice
This module have 1 configurable option.
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Copy/paste below on services.conf

# LastRegLogon [OPTIONAL]
# Module: os_lastreg
#
# Define this if you want Global to display the
# last registered nickname and channel when
# a users connect.

LastRegLogon
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

Version 1.0.0 supports Anope 1.7.18
Version 1.0.1 supports Anope 1.7.18
Version 2.0.0 supports Anope 1.7.21
